text: Such a vast difference between this interview and the interview yesterday with the foreign workers staying in the dorms. I apologise in advance if any of my words are hurtful. I hope Felix would understand that the fact he is being shifted to Expo means that he is a mild symptomatic patient, nothing too serious. The fact he is doing this interview means he is well, which is a good thing. In regards to his fever, in most stories that I've read - the fever would come and go.  The fact SG is so humid - being 38 degrees is a mild fever but nothing too serious. Felix should self monitor his fever. I think it will be more serious if Felix is experiencing breathlessness, but luckily he was not. I believe tht the medical staff who spoke to him over the phone would have send over an ambulance asap should they feel there is a need to. Felix shld understand tht during these stressful times, our healthcare workers are being stretched esp with 5k patients and rising. Everyone is working hard right now. I hope Felix gets well soon. Times are difficult right now - be grateful that our govt are doing everything they can to make sure all of the COVID-19 patient gets well. Be kind to one another. My suggestion is maybe if Felix feels he needs more attention or close monitoring - bring it up the next time they check him (if he is positive or negative before discharge).
